tern":{"recommended_structure":"[Architecture-led AI/Platform title] | [Enterprise platform design + delivery scope] | [Reliability, governance, stakeholder translation]","safe_title_families":["Solutions Architect","AI Platform Architect","Enterprise Architect","Engineering Manager","Technical Lead"],"safe_title_variants":["AI Platform Architect","Solutions Architect, AI Platforms","Enterprise Architect, AI & Data","Engineering Manager, Agentic AI","Technical Lead, AI Platforms"],"avoid_title_variants":["Head of AI without executive remit evidence","Chief AI Officer without budget/P&L ownership evidence","VP AI without multi-team org ownership evidence","Dean or academic administration titles unless that domain is truly central","KSA country-head variants without regional remit evidence"],"evidence_first_rules":["Lead with architecture proof before seniority language; title families were solutions_architect 7/16 (43.8%) and engineering_manager 5/16 (31.2%), while executive scope was only 2/16 (12.5%).","Name platform design, delivery, and production outcomes early; platform design appeared in 87.5% of the sample, and delivery/architecture were valued in 16/16 and 14/16 deep analyses.","Use people-management wording only when quantified; org building was 7/16 (43.8%), hiring 4/16 (25.0%), and budget/P&L 2/16 (12.5%).","Keep agentic AI terms subordinate to shipped outcomes; agents_orchestration, evaluation_quality, and guardrails_governance were each 2/16 (12.5%) or lower, and prompt_engineering was 0/16 (0.0%)."],"citations":["Title families: solutions_architect 7/16 (43.8%), engineering_manager 5/16 (31.2%).","Role scope: executive 2/16 (12.5%), manager 6/16 (37.5%), player_coach 2/16 (12.5%).","Architecture and delivery: platform design 87.5%; delivery 16/16 deep analyses; architecture 14/16 deep analyses."]},"tagline_profile_angle":{"positioning_angle":["Position as an architecture-led AI delivery leader who translates business goals into governed platform execution; collaboration was 13/16 (81.2%), leadership 10/16 (62.5%), and roadmap alignment appeared as a pain point in 2 samples.","Position as a player-coach only if the CV shows real team development plus hands-on platform ownership; mentoring was 8/16 (50.0%), performance management 6/16 (37.5%), and player_coach scope 2/16 (12.5%)."],"foreground":["Foreground platform design, enterprise integration, delivery, reliability, governance, and stakeholder translation; platform design was 87.5%, collaboration 13/16 (81.2%), communication 9/16 (56.2%), governance 8/16 deep analyses, and reliability 8/16 deep analyses."],"avoid":["Avoid pure executive branding without evidence; executive roles were 2/16 (12.5%), hiring 4/16 (25.0%), and budget/P&L 2/16 (12.5%).","Avoid framework-shopping profiles; each named framework appeared only 1/16 (6.2%), and prompt_engineering was 0/16 (0.0%).","Avoid academic or regional overfitting unless true; governance labels like NCAAA, QAA, RQF, TVTC, and Pearson BTEC each appeared only 2/16 (12.5%) and titles were noisy."],"safe_positioning":["Enterprise AI/platform architect with delivery ownership across design, rollout, and operational improvement; delivery evidence appeared in 16/16 deep analyses and architecture in 14/16.","Engineering leader for AI-enabled platform teams when team scope is real and quantified; leadership was 10/16 (62.5%), org building 7/16 (43.8%), and mentoring 8/16 (50.0%).","Governed AI adoption lead who embeds agentic capabilities into core tools with evaluation and guardrails; agents_orchestration, evaluation_quality, and guardrails_governance were each 2/16 (12.5%), and governance/evaluation were valued in 8/16 and 5/16 deep analyses."],"unsafe_positioning":["Large-scale AI executive with broad org, hiring, and P&L ownership when the CV is mainly technical leadership; hiring was 4/16 (25.0%) and budget/P&L 2/16 (12.5%).","Deep infrastructure operator for Kubernetes, OpenStack, or extreme compute scale without direct production proof; Kubernetes was 5/16 (31.2%) and OpenStack 3/16 (18.8%), but deep-analysis warnings flag this as unsafe when not evidenced.","AI specialist defined by RAG/prompt engineering/framework names alone; RAG was 1/16 (6.2%), prompt_engineering 0/16 (0.0%), and each named framework only 1/16 (6.2%)."],"citations":["Soft skills: collaboration 13/16 (81.2%), leadership 10/16 (62.5%), communication 9/16 (56.2%), mentoring 8/16 (50.0%).","Management leadership: org_building 7/16 (43.8%), performance_management 6/16 (37.5%), hiring 4/16 (25.0%), budget_pnl 2/16 (12.5%).","AI stack: agents_orchestration 2/16 (12.5%), evaluation_quality 2/16 (12.5%), guardrails_governance 2/16 (12.5%), prompt_engineering 0/16 (0.0%)."]},"core_competency_themes":[{"section_name":"Architecture Proof","themes":[{"theme":"Platform architecture and production design","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"This category is defined more by platform design and architecture proof than by pure title seniority; platform design appeared in 87.5% of the sample and architecture was valued in 14/16 deep analyses.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: 'platform architecture', 'solutions architecture', 'AI platform', 'enterprise architecture' 2-3 mentions across headline/profile/experience if true. Secondary keywords: 'greenfield', 'system integration', 'production rollout' 1-2 mentions. Niche tool names once only and only if true.","citation":"Platform design 87.5%; title families solutions_architect 7/16 (43.8%); architecture valued in 14/16 deep analyses."},{"theme":"Enterprise integration and system design","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"Nearby roles look more product- or model-centric; this category leans toward connecting AI capabilities into existing enterprise systems and core tooling.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: 'system design', 'enterprise integration', 'platform tooling', 'core tools' 2-3 mentions if true. Secondary keywords: 'data architecture', 'middleware', 'cross-system delivery' 1-2 mentions. Domain-specific platforms once only.","citation":"System design 3/16 (18.8%), platform tooling 3/16 (18.8%), pain point 'embed agentic AI capabilities into core tools' count=2, enterprise company stage 8/16 (50.0%)."},{"theme":"Reliability, observability, and operational health","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Reliability outcomes separate strong profiles from generic AI leadership claims because multiple pain points focus on platform health and maintainability.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: 'reliability', 'observability', 'platform health', 'performance' 2-3 mentions if true. Secondary keywords: 'SLOs', 'incident reduction', 'maintainability' 1-2 mentions. Tool-specific observability platforms once only.","citation":"Reliability valued in 8/16 deep analyses, observability 3/16 (18.8%), pain points 'keep the SaaS product performant, reliable, and maintainable' count=2 and 'improving platform reliability and observability' count=2."}]},{"section_name":"Delivery Leadership","themes":[{"theme":"Cross-functional delivery and stakeholder translation","classification":"table_stakes","why_it_matters":"The sample rewards leaders who can align technical execution to business goals, not just propose AI ideas.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: 'cross-functional delivery', 'stakeholder management', 'roadmap alignment', 'business goals' 2-3 mentions if true. Secondary keywords: 'communication', 'collaboration', 'customer-facing' 1-2 mentions. Functional-partner names once only.","citation":"Collaboration 13/16 (81.2%), communication 9/16 (56.2%), stakeholder management 6/16 (37.5%), pain point 'align engineering objectives and roadmap with business goals' count=2."},{"theme":"Mentoring and performance leadership","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"People leadership appears often enough to matter, but not strongly enough to justify inflated org-owner language unless the CV proves it.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: 'leadership', 'mentoring', 'coaching', 'performance management' 2-3 mentions if true across profile and experience. Secondary keywords: 'team development', 'career growth', 'senior/junior mix' 1-2 mentions. Hiring process terms once only unless central.","citation":"Leadership 10/16 (62.5%), mentoring 8/16 (50.0%), performance_management 6/16 (37.5%), specific domain requirement '3+ years as an engineering manager leading, coaching, and developing engineers' count=2."},{"theme":"Org shaping and hiring only when explicit","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"This can strengthen a CV, but the evidence does not support assuming broad org-building or hiring ownership for every candidate.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: 'team building', 'org design', 'hiring' 2-3 mentions only if directly true. Secondary keywords: 'headcount planning', 'interview loops', 'manager-of-managers' 1-2 mentions if true. Do not force these terms into headline if evidence is weak.","citation":"Org_building 7/16 (43.8%), hiring 4/16 (25.0%), budget_pnl 2/16 (12.5%)."}]},{"section_name":"Governed AI Adoption","themes":[{"theme":"Embedding agentic AI into real workflows","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"The category is more credible when AI is shown as integrated into products or internal operations rather than presented as abstract innovation.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: 'agentic AI', 'workflow automation', 'embedded AI', 'core tools' 2-3 mentions if true. Secondary keywords: 'orchestration', 'internal platform', 'user adoption' 1-2 mentions. Named agent frameworks once only and only if shipped.","citation":"Pain points 'build a brand new agentic AI squad' count=2 and 'embed agentic AI capabilities into core tools' count=2; agents_orchestration 2/16 (12.5%)."},{"theme":"Governance, evaluation, and guardrails","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Where AI appears, the stronger signal is controlled enterprise adoption with quality and governance, not prompt-centric experimentation.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: 'governance', 'evaluation', 'guardrails', 'quality' 2-3 mentions if true. Secondary keywords: 'policy controls', 'risk management', 'review workflows' 1-2 mentions. Specific compliance standards once only.","citation":"Evaluation_quality 2/16 (12.5%), guardrails_governance 2/16 (12.5%), governance valued in 8/16 deep analyses, evaluation valued in 5/16 deep analyses."},{"theme":"Framework fluency without framework inflation","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Framework names are too fragmented to anchor the CV; delivery evidence matters far more than naming LangChain, LangGraph, CrewAI, Dify, Coze, HiAgent, or n8n.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: use outcome words first. Secondary keywords: one or two real framework names 1-2 mentions if central. Niche framework names once only and only if true; never list a stack dump for ATS.","citation":"Each named framework appeared 1/16 (6.2%); prompt_engineering 0/16 (0.0%)."}]},{"section_name":"Technical Operating Breadth","themes":[{"theme":"Platform engineering foundations","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Several roles sit close to platform or infrastructure concerns, but no single operational keyword is universal enough to define the category.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: none are universal here. Secondary keywords: 'CI/CD', 'testing', 'Kubernetes', 'containers' 1-2 mentions each if true. Niche infrastructure terms such as 'OpenStack' once only and only with direct delivery proof.","citation":"CI/CD 5/16 (31.2%), Kubernetes 5/16 (31.2%), testing 5/16 (31.2%), containers 3/16 (18.8%), OpenStack 3/16 (18.8%)."},{"theme":"Pragmatic coding and data literacy","classification":"optional","why_it_matters":"Candidates benefit from showing enough hands-on depth to be credible with engineering teams, but the market does not show a single universal language requirement.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: if true, repeat the one or two real languages that anchor delivery 2-3 times across skills and experience. Secondary keywords: adjacent languages or data tools 1-2 mentions. Niche languages once only. There is no single universal technical keyword in this category.","citation":"Python required 4/16 (25.0%), SQL 3/16 (18.8%), Java 2/16 (12.5%), Golang preferred 3/16 (18.8%); highest hard-skill signals top out at 5/16 (31.2%)."},{"theme":"Scale, lifecycle, and cost control","classification":"differentiator","why_it_matters":"Strong profiles quantify operating outcomes such as efficiency, lifecycle management, delivery health, and cost discipline, especially in enterprise settings.","ats_guidance":"Strongest keywords: 'scale', 'efficiency', 'lifecycle management', 'cost optimization' 2-3 mentions if true. Secondary keywords: 'platform health', 'operational outcomes', 'capacity planning' 1-2 mentions. Exact cost or scale figures should appear in experience bullets, not just the skills list.","citation":"Scale valued in 11/16 deep analyses, cost in 5/16, success metrics include efficiency count=2, lifecycle management count=2, platform health count=2, operational outcomes count=2."}]}],"key_achievement_archetypes":[{"rank":1,"archetype":"Built or re-architected an AI/platform capability and put it into production","what_it_proves":"Proves the core fit for this category: architecture leadership tied to delivery, not just ideation or title inflation.","pain_points_addressed":["build a brand new agentic ai squad","embed agentic ai capabilities into core tools","align engineering objectives and roadmap with business goals"],"metrics_to_include":["time to launch","number of systems integrated","internal or customer users enabled","delivery milestones shipped","latency or throughput change if relevant"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS: name the architecture or platform problem, the integration/rollout actions you owned, and the production outcome. Show design decisions and operating results, not only feature lists.","citation":"Platform design 87.5%; delivery valued in 16/16 deep analyses; architecture 14/16; pain points for new agentic AI squad count=2 and embedding AI into core tools count=2."},{"rank":2,"archetype":"Improved reliability, observability, or maintainability of a SaaS or internal platform","what_it_proves":"Proves operating maturity and makes the CV materially different from generic GenAI leadership profiles.","pain_points_addressed":["keep the saas product performant, reliable, and maintainable","improving platform reliability and observability"],"metrics_to_include":["availability or SLO improvement","incident reduction","MTTR reduction","performance or latency improvement","maintenance load reduction"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR: define the service-health problem, the reliability levers you changed, and the before/after operating metrics. Make the metric line explicit.","citation":"Reliability valued in 8/16 deep analyses, observability 3/16 (18.8%), performance success metric count=2, platform health count=2, pain points on reliability/observability count=2 each."},{"rank":3,"archetype":"Embedded governed AI workflows with evaluation or control points","what_it_proves":"Proves practical enterprise AI adoption rather than shallow framework familiarity.","pain_points_addressed":["embed agentic ai capabilities into core tools","align engineering objectives and roadmap with business goals"],"metrics_to_include":["evaluation pass rate or quality score","adoption or active users","workflow cycle-time reduction","risk/control coverage","support ticket reduction"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS: show the workflow or business process, the governance/evaluation controls added, and the measurable adoption or quality outcome. Keep model/framework names secondary to delivery proof.","citation":"Agents_orchestration 2/16 (12.5%), evaluation_quality 2/16 (12.5%), guardrails_governance 2/16 (12.5%), governance valued in 8/16 deep analyses, evaluation in 5/16."},{"rank":4,"archetype":"Led cross-functional roadmap execution from business goal to shipped outcome","what_it_proves":"Proves translation ability between executives, product, architecture, and engineering teams.","pain_points_addressed":["align engineering objectives and roadmap with business goals","scale and manage a cross-functional engineering organization"],"metrics_to_include":["roadmap delivery rate","time-to-delivery","stakeholder satisfaction proxy","cross-team dependency reduction","business KPI moved if directly attributable"],"story_format_guidance":"Use STAR: state the business goal first, then the technical coordination challenge, then the shipped outcome with dates or metrics. Avoid vague 'partnered with stakeholders' phrasing without results.","citation":"Collaboration 13/16 (81.2%), communication 9/16 (56.2%), stakeholder management 6/16 (37.5%), pain points on roadmap alignment count=2 and cross-functional engineering organization count=2."},{"rank":5,"archetype":"Developed team capability while staying close to architecture or delivery","what_it_proves":"Proves player-coach leadership without overstating pure executive ownership.","pain_points_addressed":["scale and manage a cross-functional engineering organization","build a brand new agentic ai squad"],"metrics_to_include":["team size or span if true","retention or promotion outcomes","hiring count if true","delivery throughput improvement","mentor/coaching outcomes"],"story_format_guidance":"Use ARIS: define the team capability gap, show the coaching/performance actions you personally drove, and quantify delivery or people outcomes. Only include hiring or org design if directly evidenced.","citation":"Leadership 10/16 (62.5%), mentoring 8/16 (50.0%), performance_management 6/16 (37.5%), org_building 7/16 (43.8%), hiring 4/16 (25.0%)."}],"role_weighting_guidance":{"highest_weight_roles":["Weight architecture-led roles highest: solutions_architect was 7/16 (43.8%) and platform design appeared in 87.5% of the sample.","Weight engineering-manager roles second when they include delivery ownership and technical depth: engineering_manager was 5/16 (31.2%) and manager scope 6/16 (37.5%).","Weight enterprise/data architecture roles when they show integration, governance, or modernization outcomes in enterprise environments; enterprise company stage appeared in 8/16 (50.0%) and governance in 8/16 deep analyses."],"expand_in_work_history":["Expand roles where you designed or modernized platforms, owned production delivery, or integrated AI into existing systems; delivery was valued in 16/16 deep analyses and architecture in 14/16.","Expand bullets with reliability, observability, scale, lifecycle, or cost outcomes when true; reliability appeared in 8/16 deep analyses, scale in 11/16, and cost in 5/16.","Expand team-lead or manager roles only when they include coaching, performance, or org-shaping evidence; leadership was 10/16 (62.5%), mentoring 8/16 (50.0%), performance management 6/16 (37.5%)."],"compress_in_work_history":["Compress roles that are purely academic-administration or compliance-heavy unless that sector is truly targeted; academic administration appeared only 2/16 (12.5%) and governance labels such as NCAAA/QAA/RQF/TVTC/Pearson BTEC each only 2/16 (12.5%).","Compress generic tool-list bullets that do not show delivery or operating outcomes; each named AI framework appeared only 1/16 (6.2%).","Compress legacy hands-on infrastructure detail unless it directly supports current platform credibility; no hard skill exceeded 5/16 (31.2%), so long stack inventories do not anchor the category."],"how_to_frame_non_ai_experience":["Frame non-AI roles as evidence of platform architecture, system integration, reliability, or governed delivery that later made AI adoption credible; architecture was valued in 14/16 deep analyses and delivery in 16/16.","Frame consulting or enterprise architecture work around business-to-technical translation and rollout outcomes, not generic advisory language; collaboration was 13/16 (81.2%) and stakeholder management 6/16 (37.5%).","Frame infrastructure or platform work around operational outcomes, lifecycle, and scale, but avoid extreme-scale or niche-platform claims unless directly evidenced; scale was valued in 11/16 deep analyses and unsafe-claim analysis explicitly warns against inflated infra ownership."],"citations":["Title families: solutions_architect 7/16 (43.8%), engineering_manager 5/16 (31.2%).","Architecture and delivery: platform design 87.5%; delivery 16/16 deep analyses; architecture 14/16.","Management: leadership 10/16 (62.5%), mentoring 8/16 (50.0%), performance_management 6/16 (37.5%), hiring 4/16 (25.0%)."]},"language_and_tone":{"recommended_tone":"architect","formality":"high","preferred_vocabulary":["platform architecture","enterprise integration","production delivery","reliability","governance","evaluation","stakeholder alignment","operational outcomes","team development","AI platform"],"avoid_vocabulary":["visionary","thought leader","best-in-class","AI evangelist","prompt guru","ninja","rockstar","disruptive innovation"],"citations":["Architecture-led pattern: solutions_architect 7/16 (43.8%), platform design 87.5%, architecture valued in 14/16 deep analyses.","Enterprise/operating orientation: enterprise company stage 8/16 (50.0%), reliability 8/16 deep analyses, governance 8/16 deep analyses.","Leadership should stay measured: executive scope 2/16 (12.5%), budget/P&L 2/16 (12.5%)."]},"unsafe_or_weak_framing":{"avoid_claims":["Leading a large infrastructure team with broad direct-report scope unless team size and management depth are explicit in the CV.","Deep production Go ownership unless shipped Go systems are clearly evidenced.","Operating Kubernetes, OpenStack, or extreme-scale compute environments without direct production proof.","Owning OKRs, KPIs, or platform-health metrics without concrete numbers.","Owning Databricks, Microsoft Fabric, Power BI embedded, customer 360/MDM, Neo4j, or AKS implementations without direct delivery evidence.","Claiming TOGAF or SAFe certification unless explicitly held."],"buzzword_patterns":["Do not stack 'GenAI, LLMs, RAG, agents, LangChain, LangGraph, CrewAI' without a shipped architecture and outcome line; each framework appeared only 1/16 (6.2%).","Do not make prompt engineering the center of the profile; prompt_engineering was 0/16 (0.0%).","Do not use 'Head of AI' branding to mask a profile that is really senior IC or architecture-led; executive scope was 2/16 (12.5%)."],"title_inflation_risks":["Inflating to 'Head of AI', 'VP AI', or 'Chief AI Officer' is risky without multi-team executive ownership, hiring, and budget evidence.","Inflating to country or regional ownership is risky without explicit KSA remit evidence.","Using academic dean-style titles is risky outside that sector because titles were noisy and the core archetype is architecture-led, not academic administration."],"research_framing_risks":["Do not add PhD, research, or publication framing as a positive angle; research_heavy was 0/16 (0.0%) and requires_phd was 12.5%.","Do not present the category as research-led AI strategy; the evidence favors delivery, architecture, governance, and reliability."],"domain_or_region_risks":["Do not overfit to education-sector compliance labels such as NCAAA, QAA, RQF, TVTC, or Pearson BTEC unless directly relevant; each appeared only 2/16 (12.5%).","Do not imply Arabic or native-language requirements; native_language_requirements were absent.","Do not imply cultural-intelligence or KSA-specific operating fluency unless directly evidenced; cultural intelligence appeared only 2/16 (12.5%)."],"citations":["Deep-analysis unsafe claims flag inflated infra/team/Go/OKR/certification claims repeatedly; top items each appeared 2 times.","Research-heavy_pct 0.0%; requires_phd_pct 12.5%.","Named frameworks each 1/16 (6.2%); prompt_engineering 0/16 (0.0%); compliance labels each 2/16 (12.5%)."]},"evidence_ledger":[{"recommendation":"Use an architect-led headline and profile before any executive wording.","support":["Solutions_architect title family 7/16 (43.8%) exceeds executive 2/16 (12.5%).","Platform design appeared in 87.5% of the sample.","Architecture was valued in 14/16 deep analyses."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Show production delivery and architecture outcomes in the first third of the CV.","support":["Delivery evidence appeared in 16/16 deep analyses.","Architecture evidence appeared in 14/16 deep analyses.","Greenfield/optimization signal shows build-and-improve scope: both=10, optimization=3."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Quantify reliability, scale, lifecycle, and operational health where true.","support":["Scale was valued in 11/16 deep analyses.","Reliability was valued in 8/16 deep analyses.","Success metrics repeatedly referenced reliability, efficiency, lifecycle management, operational outcomes, and platform health (each count=2)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Keep people-leadership claims measured unless team scope is explicit.","support":["Leadership 10/16 (62.5%) and mentoring 8/16 (50.0%) support leadership language.","Hiring 4/16 (25.0%) and budget/P&L 2/16 (12.5%) do not support broad executive-owner assumptions.","Role scope mixes manager 6/16 (37.5%) with IC 5/16 (31.2%)."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Use governed AI adoption as a differentiator only when shipped outcomes are real.","support":["Agents_orchestration 2/16 (12.5%), evaluation_quality 2/16 (12.5%), and guardrails_governance 2/16 (12.5%) are present but not universal.","Governance was valued in 8/16 deep analyses and evaluation in 5/16.","Prompt_engineering was 0/16 (0.0%)."],"confidence":"medium"},{"recommendation":"Do not anchor the CV around a single technical keyword; use truthful stack terms selectively.","support":["No hard skill exceeded 5/16 (31.2%).","Python reached only 4/16 (25.0%) and SQL 3/16 (18.8%).","Framework signals were fragmented at 1/16 (6.2%) each."],"confidence":"high"},{"recommendation":"Avoid overfitting the CV to academic or KSA-specific compliance unless the candidate truly targets that niche.","support":["Noisy title mode is true.","Academic administration appeared 2/16 (12.5%).","NCAAA, QAA, RQF, TVTC, and Pearson BTEC each appeared 2/16 (12.5%)."],"confidence":"medium"}  ,{"recommendation":"Differentiate this category from adjacent AI leadership categories by emphasizing enterprise integration, platform health, and stakeholder translation over model-centric or research-centric framing.","support":["Collaboration 13/16 (81.2%) and communication 9/16 (56.2%) are stronger than any model-specific keyword.","Enterprise company stage appeared in 8/16 (50.0%).","Research_heavy_pct is 0.0% and delivery/architecture dominate the deep-analysis evidence."],"confidence":"high"}  ,{"recommendation":"Treat this blueprint as directional rather than rigid because sample confidence is not high.","support":["Confidence is medium.","Titles are noisy and inconsistent with the category label.","User rule for sparse categories applies when confidence != high."],"confidence":"high"}  ,{"recommendation":"If the candidate truly has player-coach experience, show both technical authority and team development in the same stories.","support":["Role scope includes player_coach 2/16 (12.5%).","Leadership 10/16 (62.5%), mentoring 8/16 (50.0%), and performance management 6/16 (37.5%) support mixed technical/leadership stories.","Candidate-safe framing matters because deep analysis repeatedly flags inflated management claims as unsafe."],"confidence":"medium"}]}
